 the expansion of cricket, encouraging international competition and fostering a sense of unity among cricket fans.<br/>Despite its popularity, the Cricket World Cup faces challenges such as scheduling conflicts, player fatigue, and maintaining viewer interest. The ICC has worked to address these issues, exploring new formats and making adjustments to keep the tournament engaging and relevant. The future success of the Cricket World Cup will depend on its ability to adapt to changing trends while maintaining its status as the ultimate competition in limited-overs cricket.' +
